  "commentary": "With SPX at 6572 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-8.8B) and positive gamma resistance at 6600 (+8.9B), dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they're short gamma in this zone. The breakout regime with -14.8B total GEX means any move will be amplified - a push above 6600 forces dealer selling into strength while a break below 6550 triggers more dealer buying that could accelerate downside momentum. Watch 6550 as the critical floor and 6600 as the ceiling, with 6580 (+6.4B) acting as interim resistance.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 and 6600 with big moves likely once either level breaks.",
